Then
\begin{align*}
x + y &= AB + AC \\
&= BT_3 + CT_3 \\
&= 2 \cdot T_3B \\
&= 2 \cdot \sqrt{5^2 - (\tfrac{7}{2})^2} \\
&= 2 \cdot \sqrt{\tfrac{225}{4}} \\
&= 15.
\end{align*}By the Power of a Point formula, $AT_1 \cdot AT_2 = AB \cdot AC = xy,$ so $AT_1 \cdot AT_2 \le \tfrac{(x+y)^2}{4} = \tfrac{225}{4}.$  Then $AT_1 + AT_2 \le \tfrac{15}{2},$ so by AM-GM,
\[BC = 7 = AT_1 + AT_2 + 2T_1T_2 \le \frac{15}{2} + 2 \cdot \sqrt{\frac{225}{4}} = 20.\]Therefore, $BC = 7$ implies $x = y = \tfrac{15}{2},$ so $AB + AC = \boxed{15}.$

