Then by the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $BMC,$
\[\left( \frac{1}{3} x \right)^2 + 8^2 = \left( \frac{2}{3} x \right)^2.\]This simplifies to $x^2 = 243,$ so $AD = 2x = \boxed{6 \sqrt{3}}.$

