Then the area of the cross section $x$ feet from the apex is proportional to the square of the distance of that cross section from the apex.  Hence,
\[\frac{A}{B} = \left( \frac{h}{h + 8} \right)^2.\]Solving for $h,$ we find
\[h = \frac{8 \sqrt{A}}{\sqrt{B} - \sqrt{A}}.\]Then
\[h = \frac{8 \sqrt{216\sqrt{3}}}{\sqrt{486\sqrt{3}} - \sqrt{216\sqrt{3}}} = \boxed{36}.\]
